The following post is not meant to be constructive in any way, shape, or form:<P>Fuck 'em all. If I had the go ahead there would not be a Middle-East. I would blow them all up. Eventually the Middle-East will be destroyed. All of it. Why? As soon as NY or DC is blown up by a nuke we will have justification.  Sssorn's solution is great.  What he is discussing is another issue entirely and I totally support him as it works right NOW. Mine is not constructive to the current situation nor is it hopeful in the sense we are "waiting for a nuke to blow up in a major U.S. city." Quite frankly, I don't even know why I said this, I've mentioned it before. I feel compelled to mention it again. I guess I'm just pissed off. F the Civil Liberties Union, F soccer moms and clueless people, F everyone who is full of their PC bullshit, F power politics... for once in our lives we need to do what is in our best intrest. Wipe the Middle-East off the map before they kill 7 million New Yorkers in a matter of seconds.  So your one of those PC, tree hugging clueless pacifists? Well let me describe some of your possible feelings if we did go ahead and blow up the Middle-East now. You might be "upset" that we commited genocide or rather a crusade against a whole other culture and relgion...but guess what? That pain will go away. Your children might scold your generations actions but even that will subside. I think this is a price we should be willing to pay.  I care about us folks. The United State of America. What it stands for. Above all our SAFETY. nothing else. It is nearly inevitable a nuclear bomb will be planted and detonated in a major city more than likely New York or Washington D.C. Millions will die. This will happen UNLESS we do something now.<P>I hope to not seem like a right wing militarist but I can't help it any more. Sorry for not using paragraph spacing. Best wishes in whatever your opinions are but a nuke will go off, the question is which side first?<p>[ May 23, 2002: Mes