<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
As I have mentioned before to other of our service men and women out there, you have our undying support and admiration.  You my friend, are a real hero.<P>           <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>First, we fight AGAINST genocide NOT promote it. We don’t smack your dad in the face when the word "fuck" came out of YOUR mouth. We go straight after the black sheep not the WHOLE heard.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Although this mentality is noble, it is flawed.  Terrorists exploit this mentality.  They do so by hiding that black sheep among the herd, and exploit the fact that we wouldn't harm the herd because it is "innocent" after all.  Even if we do catch the black sheep, it doesn't matter since the herd itself has become a "black sheep factory" basically, with a mind to produce as many black sheep as possible under the veil of the herd's "innocence."  If the world adheres to your mentality, then there will be no stopping the proliferation of black sheep (terrorism) throughout the world.  The herd must be deterred, no matter how innocent it purports to be.<P>Further, “genocide” is the deliberate and systematic destruction of a racial, political, or cultural group.  In some instances, genocide is justified and correct, such as the destruction of the political group known as the nazis and the cultural group known as nazism.  I think what you meant to say is we fight against the deliberate and systematic destruction of INNOCENT racial, political or cultural groups.   I don’t disagree.  However, this is not our #1 priority.  It is secondary to our #1 priority which is protecting America.  If innocents must die to protect America, then provided we do everything in our power to prevent their death, if innocents ultimately do die because we have no choice, so be it.  As mentioned, terrorists exploit these two priorities by putting them in conflict.  By hiding as they do amidst their “innocents,” they force us to choose between either protecting America and killing their innocents, or failing to adequately protect America.<P>Let me give you a better analogy.<P>A good man walks out of the saloon into the dirt street to have a gun duel with an outlaw.  The good man’s family is standing along the side of the road watching, as is the outlaw’s.  The good man does not believe in the killing of innocents.  But he does believe in protecting his family and himself.<P>OK now imagine that the outlaw is a nazi.  How did the nazi’s fight?  Straight up.  They said "Here is our return address, and here we are.  Bring the noise if you wish to challenge us because here we come."  In other words, the nazi outlaw lined up for a fair gun battle to the death, if you can call it that.  When they drew their guns, the nazi took some shots not only at the good man, but at his family too, killing innocents.  But at least the nazi outlaw exposed himself and stood alone on that street, and was killed by the good man with a shot between the eyes.<P>OK now imagine that the outlaw is a terrorist.  How do terrorists fight?  They attack, then hide among their people, who give them support and encouragement.  In other words, right before the terrorist outlaw draws his gun, he runs over, grabs his mother, brings her out to the street, and holds her in front of him like a human hostage.  <BR>The gun battle starts.  <BR>The good man does not shoot because he does not want to kill the innocent mother.  <BR>The terrorist points his gun at the good man’s son, and blows him away.  <BR>The good man still does not shoot because he does not want to kill the terrorist’s innocent mother.  <BR>The good man says "Madame, please step away, and deliver your son before me so that I may defend my family without harming you."<BR>The mother laughs and ignores him, since after all, since she was the one who raised her son to behave in this way.  <BR>The terrorist points his gun at the good man’s daughter, and blows her away.  <BR>The good man still does not shoot because he does not want to kill the terrorist’s innocent mother.  <BR>The terrorist points his gun at the good man’s father, and blows him away.  <BR>The terrorist laughs.<BR>The good man realizes this cannot go on.  He tries to save the innocent woman and says: “I am sorry, but you cannot continue killing my innocent family like this while hiding behind your mother.  Please step away from behind her or both of you must die.”  <BR>The terrorist laughs.  <BR>The mother laughs.<BR>The terrorist shoots the good man’s mother between the eyes.<P>At what point is the good man entitled to shoot the terrorist and be excused from the death of the terrorist’s mother as a consequence?  At what point is the good man entitled to tell the world that sorry, one may not hide behind one’s innocent friends and family as an effective way to avoid retribution, while deliberately killing and mutilating hundreds and thousands of innocents?<P>The “terrorist mother” in this analogy is, ofcourse, Arab subcultures wherein the fanaticism of hate, martyrdom and jihad are bred.  America, as the good man, would ask these counties to hand over the terrorists and more importantly, remove the institutionalization of jihad (i.e., the mentality that has transformed the herd into a terrorism factory), akin to asking the terrorist mother to “step aside.”  Naturally, they would not step aside, and their death, and the death of their innocents, would be justified under these circumstances I am afraid.<P>There is simply no other way, because terrorism is unacceptable and must be adequately deterred.  This is the only way.  Terrorists must be deterred, and if their families and friends take part in promulgating jihad, then they must be held accountable, much in the way dog owners must be held accountable for the harm their dogs cause, regardless how innocent the owners are.<p>[ May 24, 2002: Message edited by: Lizard ]<P>--------------------<P>Scaled, for her pleasure<BR><A HREF="http://drow.org/eq/roster/viewprofile.php?name=Sssorn" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A> | <A HREF="http://www.drow.org/news.shtml" TARGET=_blank>BotS</A>
